17 (10) a mother-in-law or father-in-law; or
18 (11) a first cousin.
19 (c) Except as provided in subsections (d) through (k), a person who
20 knowingly or intentionally:
21 (1) touches another person in a rude, insolent, or angry manner;
22 or
23 (2) in a rude, insolent, or angry manner places any bodily fluid or
24 waste on another person;
25 commits battery, a Class B misdemeanor.
26 (d) The offense described in subsection (c)(1) or (c)(2) is a Class A
27 misdemeanor if it:
