1 (11) any aerosol generated form of liquids listed in this
2 subsection.
3 (b) As used in this section, "infectious hepatitis" means:
4 (1) hepatitis A;
5 (2) hepatitis B;
6 (3) hepatitis C;
7 (4) hepatitis D;
8 (5) hepatitis E; or
9 (6) hepatitis G.
10 (c) A person who recklessly, knowingly, or intentionally places
11 human:
12 (1) body fluid; or
13 (2) fecal waste;
14 in a location with the intent that another person will involuntarily touch
15 the body fluid or fecal waste commits malicious mischief, a Class B
16 misdemeanor.
17 (d) An offense described in subsection (c) is a:
18 (1) Level 6 felony if the person knew or recklessly failed to know
19 that the body fluid or fecal waste was infected with:
20 (A) infectious hepatitis; or
21 (B) HIV; or
22 (C) (B) tuberculosis; and
23 (2) Level 5 felony if:
24 (A) the person knew or recklessly failed to know that the body
25 fluid or fecal waste was infected with infectious hepatitis and
26 the offense results in the transmission of infectious hepatitis to
27 the other person; or
28 (B) the person knew or recklessly failed to know that the body
29 fluid or fecal waste was infected with tuberculosis and the
30 offense results in the transmission of tuberculosis to the other
31 person. and
32 (3) Level 4 felony if:
33 (A) the person knew or recklessly failed to know that the body
34 fluid or fecal waste was infected with HIV; and
35 (B) the offense results in the transmission of HIV to the other
36 person.
37 (e) A person who recklessly, knowingly, or intentionally places
38 human:
39 (1) body fluid; or
40 (2) fecal waste;
41 in a location with the intent that another person will ingest the body
42 fluid or fecal waste commits malicious mischief with food, a Class A
